## 1. Project Overview

**Project Name:** Loan Tracker Web Application
**Purpose:**
A web-based application that allows users to manually record, manage, and track loans they have given to other individuals. The system focuses on loan tracking, history preservation, and reminders — not payments or lending transactions.

**Technology Stack:**

* Frontend: React + TypeScript
* Styling: Tailwind CSS
* Platform: Web-only (responsive)
* Authentication: Email & Password

---

## 2. Target Users & Roles

### User Roles

1. **Borrower (Regular User)**

   * Can create, view, update, and delete their own loans
   * Can mark loans as completed
   * Can export their loan data
   * Can view dashboards and notifications related to their loans

2. **Super Admin**

   * Can view all loans across all users
   * Can manage users
   * Can perform full CRUD operations on any loan
   * Can impersonate users if required

**No staff/agent role is required.**

---

## 3. Authentication & Authorization

* Users must **register first** using email and password
* Users must log in to access the application
* Role-based access control must be enforced
* No social login
* No OTP-based authentication

---

## 4. Core Features

### Loan Management

* Add New Loan button available on dashboard
* Users can manage multiple loans
* All loan data is entered manually (no auto-calculation)

### Loan Fields

Each loan record must include:

1. Borrower Name
2. Actual Loan Amount (INR)
3. Interest Amount (INR)
4. Given Date
5. Due Date
6. Notes (optional, free text)
7. Loan Status:

   * Active
   * Overdue
   * Completed

---

## 5. Repayment & Loan History Rules

* Repayment status is managed manually
* Users can mark loans as completed
* Missed payments can include penalties (manual entry)
* If a loan is extended:

  * Previous due dates must be preserved
  * Previous interest amounts must be preserved
  * Extension history must be visible for reference
* Loan history must never be overwritten

---

## 6. Notifications

### Notification Types

* Upcoming due date reminders
* Overdue loan alerts

### Notification Channels

* In-app notifications
* Email notifications

**No SMS or push notifications.**

---

## 7. Dashboard & UI Requirements

### Design Style

* Modern / fintech-style UI
* Clean, card-based layout
* Responsive across desktop and mobile
* No dark mode
* No predefined branding assets

### Dashboard Components

* Summary cards:

  * Total loans
  * Active loans
  * Overdue loans
  * Completed loans

### Loan Listing

* Card-based loan list
* Each loan card must include action buttons:

  * View details
  * Edit
  * Export
  * Delete
  * Mark as completed

---

## 8. Reporting & Exporting

* Users can view:

  * Loan summaries
  * Loan history timelines
* Export options:

  * PDF
  * Excel / CSV
* Admin can export system-wide loan data

---

## 9. Data Management & Retention

* Loan data is stored until the user deletes it
* Deleted loans are permanently removed
* No archiving
* No soft delete

---

## 10. Integrations

* No payment gateway integration
* No banking APIs
* No accounting software integrations
* CSV / Excel export only

---

## 11. Non-Functional Requirements

* Expected users: ~10
* Currency: INR only
* Performance: Fast load times (ASAP)
* No multi-language support
* No AI or predictive features

---

## 12. Out of Scope (Explicitly Excluded)

* Payments inside the app
* EMI auto-calculation
* Credit scoring
* Dark mode
* Mobile native apps

